==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Catoptromancy
<hw>Ca*top"tro*man`cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/
mirror + <ets>-mancy</ets>. See <er>Catopter</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Antiq.)</fld> <def>A species of divination, which was performed by
letting down a mirror into water, for a sick person to look at his face
in it. If his countenance appeared distorted and ghastly, it was an ill
omen; if fresh and healthy, it was favorable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Catoptron</ent>⟦br⟧
